New Records: Damian Lillard scored 34 points and Giannis Antetokounmpo added 31 points in the Milwaukee Bucks' 123-100 victory over the Utah Jazz, snapping their six-game losing streak.
Key Match Events: The dynamic duo of Lillard and Antetokounmpo dominated the third quarter, contributing 22 of the team's 31 points. The Bucks maintained an 11-point cushion from the start of the fourth quarter to the end, securing a commanding victory.
